{"text": "i\n\n\n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    3G Capital - Contact\n    \n    \n     \n\n\n    \n        \n        \n        \n            \n                About\n                Approach\n                Partners\n                    \n                        Founding Partners\n                        Partners\n                    \n                \n                Acquisitions\n                    \n                        Burger King\n                        H.J. Heinz Company\n                        Restaurant Brands International\n                        Kraft Heinz Company\n                    \n                \n                Contact\n                Investor Login\n            \n        \n        \n        \n            \n                \n                    \n                        CONTACT\n                    \n                        New York\n                    \n                        600 Third Avenue, 37 Floor\n                        New York, NY, 10016\n                        Phone: +1 212-893-6727\n                        Email: info(at)3g-capital.com\n                    \n                    \n                        Rio de Janeiro\n                    \n                        Rua Humait\u00e1, 275 / 9\u00ba andar\n                        Rio de Janeiro, RJ, 22261-001\n                        Phone: +55 21-3515-6227\n                        Email: info(at)3g-capital.com\n                \n                \n            \n            \n        \n        \n        \n        \n    \n    \n    \n        \n            Copyright \u00a9 2010-                                            var theDate = new Date();\n                                            document.write(theDate.getFullYear()); \n                3G Capital. All Rights Reserved. | Legal Notices and Terms of Use.", "page": ["3G Capital - Contact"]}
{"text": "About\n                Approach\n                Partners\n                    \n                        Founding Partners\n                        Partners\n                    \n                \n                Acquisitions\n                    \n                        Burger King\n                        H.J. Heinz Company\n                        Restaurant Brands International\n                        Kraft Heinz Company\n                    \n                \n                Contact\n                Investor Login\n            \n        \n        \n        \n            \n                \n                    \n                        Burger King Holdings\n                    \n                        MIAMI and NEW YORK - September 2, 2010 - Burger King Holdings, Inc. (NYSE: BKC)\n                        (the \"Company\") and 3G Capital today announced that they have entered into a definitive\n                        agreement under which affiliates of 3G Capital will acquire the stock of the Company\n                        for $24.00 per share, or $4.0 billion, including the assumption of the Company's\n                        outstanding debt.\n                    \n                    \n                        Alex Behring, Managing Partner of 3G Capital, said, \"We have great respect for the\n                        Burger King\u00ae brand and the strong business that management, the employees and\n                        the franchisees have built. The iconic Burger King\u00ae brand, its solid franchisee\n                        network and great product offerings make this a perfect fit for 3G Capital, which\n                        has a strong track record of long-term investments in global consumer brands and\n                        retail companies. We are excited to work together with the Company's employees and\n                        franchisees to continue to invest in the brand for the benefit of all its guests,\n                        employees and franchisees.\"\n                    \n                    \n                        Visit the Burger King website at www.bk.com\n                    \n                \n                \n            \n            \n        \n        \n        \n        \n    \n    \n    \n        \n            Copyright \u00a9 2010-                                            var theDate = new Date();\n                                            document.write(theDate.getFullYear()); \n                3G Capital. All Rights Reserved. | Legal Notices and Terms of Use.", "page": ["3G Capital - Burger King"]}
{"text": "About\n                Approach\n                Partners\n                    \n                        Founding Partners\n                        Partners\n                    \n                \n                Acquisitions\n                    \n                        Burger King\n                        H.J. Heinz Company\n                        Restaurant Brands International\n                        Kraft Heinz Company\n                    \n                \n                Contact\n                Investor Login\n            \n        \n        \n        \n            \n                \n                    Kraft Heinz Company\n                    \n                    PITTSBURGH, Pa. and NORTHFIELD, Ill. \u2013 July 2, 2015 \u2013 The Kraft Heinz Company (NASDAQ: KHC) is pleased to announce the successful completion of the merger between Kraft Foods Group and H.J. Heinz Holding Corporation.\n                    The transaction creates the third-largest food and beverage company in North America and the fifth-largest food and beverage company in the world with an unparalleled portfolio of iconic brands. The complementary nature of the two brand portfolios presents substantial opportunity for synergies, which will result in increased investments in marketing and innovation. This historic transaction unites two powerful businesses and iconic brands, and provides a platform for leadership in the food industry both domestically and internationally.\n                    \n                    \n                        View the press release\n                    \n                    \n                    \n                    \n                        Visit the Kraft Heinz Company web site: www.kraftheinzcompany.com\n                    \n                \n                \n            \n            \n        \n        \n        \n        \n    \n    \n    \n        \n            Copyright \u00a9 2010-                                            var theDate = new Date();\n                                            document.write(theDate.getFullYear()); \n                3G Capital. All Rights Reserved. | Legal Notices and Terms of Use.", "page": ["3G Capital - Kraft Heinz Company"]}
{"text": "About\n                Approach\n                Partners\n                    \n                        Founding Partners\n                        Partners\n                    \n                \n                Acquisitions\n                    \n                        Burger King\n                        H.J. Heinz Company\n                        Restaurant Brands International\n                        Kraft Heinz Company\n                    \n                \n                Contact\n                Investor Login\n            \n        \n        \n        \n            \n                \n                    \n                        FOUNDING PARTNERS\n                    \n                        \n                            Jorge Paulo Lemann\n                        \n                            Co-founder and Board Member of 3G Capital since late 2004\n                            Controlling shareholder and Board Member of Anheuser-Busch InBev\n                            Board Member of The Kraft Heinz Company since June 2013\n                            Founding shareholder and principal executive of Banco de Investimentos Garantia in Brazil\n                                from 1971 through July 1998, when it was sold to Credit Suisse First Boston\n                            Co-founder and Partner of GP Investimentos (Brazilian private equity firm) until\n                                2004\n                            Controlling shareholder and Board Member of Lojas Americanas from 1983 to 2005\n                            Board Member of The Gillette Company from 1998-2005\n                            Board Member of Swiss Reinsurance from 1999-2005\n                            Former International Advisory Board Member of DaimlerChrysler and Credit Suisse\n                                Group\n                            Former Chairman of the Latin American Advisory Board of the New York Stock Exchange\n                            Member of the Advisory Board of Harvard Business School\n                            Founding Board Member of Funda\u00e7\u00e3o Estudar, a foundation that provides\n                                scholarships to needy students\n                            BA from Harvard University\n                        \n                    \n                    \n                        \n                            Carlos Alberto Sicupira\n                        \n                            Co-founder and Board Member of 3G Capital since late 2004\n                            Controlling shareholder and Board Member of Anheuser-Busch InBev, previously Ambev\n                            Partner of Banco de Investimentos Garantia in Brazil from 1976 through July 1998, when it was sold to Credit\n                                Suisse First Boston\n                            Co-founder and Managing Partner of GP Investimentos (Brazilian private equity firm)\n                                from 1993 to 2004\n                            Board Member of Burger King since October 2010\n                            Controlling shareholder and Chairman of Lojas Americanas since 1983; CEO from 1983 to 1991\n                            Board Member of B2W (internet retail company operating Americanas.com and Submarino)\n                                since March 2007\n                            Member of the Board of the Associates of Harvard Business School since 1988\n                            BA from Federal University of Rio de Janeiro, Brazil\n                            OPM from Harvard University\n                        \n                    \n                    \n                        \n                            Marcel Herrmann Telles\n                        \n                            Co-founder and Board Member of 3G Capital since late 2004\n                            Controlling shareholder and Board Member of Anheuser-Busch InBev, previously Ambev; former Chairman and CEO of Ambev\n                            Partner of Banco de Investimentos Garantia in Brazil from 1976 through July 1998, when it was sold to Credit\n                                Suisse First Boston; Head Trader from 1974 to 1989\n                            Board Member of The Kraft Heinz Company since June 2013\n                            Board Member of Burger King from 2010 to 2013\n                            Board Member of Lojas Americanas\n                            Partner of GP Investimentos (Brazilian private equity firm) until 2004\n                            BA from Universidade Federal do Rio de Janeiro\n                            OPM from Harvard University\n                        \n                    \n                    \n                        \n                            Roberto Thompson Motta\n                        \n                            Co-founder and Board Member of 3G Capital since late 2004\n                            Board Member of Anheuser-Busch InBev and Ambev\n                            Board Member of Burger King since June 2013\n                            Board Member of Lojas Americanas\n                            Board Member of S\u00e3o Carlos Empreendimentos e Participa\u00e7\u00f5es\n                            Co-founder and Partner of GP Investimentos (Brazilian private equity firm) from\n                                1993 to 2004\n                            BS in Engineering from Pontif\u00edcia Universidade Cat\u00f3lica do Rio de\n                                Janeiro\n                            MBA from The Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania\n                        \n                    \n                    \n                        \n                            Alex Behring\n                        \n                            Co-founder, Managing Partner, and Board Member of 3G Capital since late 2004\n                            Chairman and Board Member of Restaurant Brands International since 3G Capital's acquisition of Burger King in October 2010 and following Burger King's subsequent acquisition of Tim Hortons in December 2014\n                            Chairman and Board Member of The Kraft Heinz Company since Berkshire Hathaway and 3G Capital's acquisition of HJ Heinz Company in June 2013 and subsequent combination with Kraft Foods Group in July 2015\n                            Board Member of Anheuser-Busch InBev since April 2014\n                            Board Member of CSX from 2008 \u2013 2011\n                            Co-founder, Board Member of America Latina Logistica (ALL) from 1996 \u2013 2011; CEO from 1998 \u2013 2004\n                            Partner and board member of GP Investimentos from 1994 \u2013 2004\n                            Co-founder and Managing Partner of Modus OSI Technologies from 1988 \u2013 1993\n                            MBA, Baker Scholar, from Harvard Graduate School of Business, Boston, MA\n                            BS in Electric Engineering from PUC, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil\n                        \n                    \n                \n                \n            \n            \n            \n                \n                    Alex Behring\n                    Jorge Paulo Lemann\n                    Carlos Alberto Sicupira\n                    Marcel Herrmann Telles\n                    Roberto Thompson Motta\n                \n            \n            \n        \n        \n        \n        \n    \n    \n    \n        \n            Copyright \u00a9 2010-                                            var theDate = new Date();\n                                            document.write(theDate.getFullYear()); \n                3G Capital. All Rights Reserved. | Legal Notices and Terms of Use.", "page": ["3G Capital - Founding Partners"]}
{"text": "About\n                Approach\n                Partners\n                    \n                        Founding Partners\n                        Partners\n                    \n                \n                Acquisitions\n                    \n                        Burger King\n                        H.J. Heinz Company\n                        Restaurant Brands International\n                        Kraft Heinz Company\n                    \n                \n                Contact\n                Investor Login\n            \n        \n        \n        \n            \n                \n                    Restaurant Brands International\n                    \n                    \n                        OAKVILLE, Ontario - December 12, 2014 - Restaurant Brands International Inc. (TSX, NYSE: QSR) is pleased to announce the successful completion of the transaction with Tim Hortons Inc. (TSX, NYSE: THI) and Burger King Worldwide, Inc. (BKW). The transaction creates Restaurant Brands International, a new global quick service restaurant leader operating two iconic, independent brands.\n                        . . . .\n                    \n                    \n                        About Restaurant Brands International\n                        Restaurant Brands International is one of the world's largest quick service restaurant companies with approximately $23 billion in system sales and over 18,000 restaurants in 100 countries. Restaurant Brands International owns two of the world\u2019s most prominent and iconic quick service restaurant brands \u2013 Tim Hortons\u00ae and Burger King\u00ae. These independently operated brands have been serving their respective guests, franchisees, and communities for over 50 years.\n                    \n                    \n                        About Tim Hortons Inc.\n                        Tim Hortons\u00ae is one of the largest restaurant chains in North America and the largest in Canada. Operating in the quick service segment of the restaurant industry, Tim Hortons\u00ae appeals to a broad range of consumer tastes, with a menu that includes premium coffee, hot and cold specialty drinks (including lattes, cappuccinos and espresso shots), specialty teas and fruit smoothies, fresh baked goods, grilled Panini and classic sandwiches, wraps, soups, prepared foods and other food products. As of September 28, 2014, Tim Hortons\u00ae had 4,590 system wide restaurants, including 3,665 in Canada, 869 in the United States and 56 in the Gulf Cooperation Council. \n                    \n\n                    \n                        About Burger King Worldwide, Inc.\n                        Founded in 1954, Burger King\u00ae is the second largest fast food hamburger chain in the world. The original Home of the Whopper, the Burger King\u00ae system operates in approximately 14,000 locations serving more than 11 million guests daily in 100 countries and territories worldwide. Approximately 100 percent of Burger King\u00ae restaurants are owned and operated by independent franchisees, many of them family-owned operations that have been in business for decades.\n\n                    \n                    \n                        Visit the Restaurant Brands International website at www.rbi.com\n                    \n\n                \n                \n            \n            \n        \n        \n        \n        \n    \n    \n    \n        \n            Copyright \u00a9 2010-                                            var theDate = new Date();\n                                            document.write(theDate.getFullYear()); \n                3G Capital. All Rights Reserved. | Legal Notices and Terms of Use.", "page": ["3G Capital - Restaurant Brands International"]}
{"text": "About\n                Approach\n                Partners\n                    \n                        Founding Partners\n                        Partners\n                    \n                \n                Acquisitions\n                    \n                        Burger King\n                        H.J. Heinz Company\n                        Restaurant Brands International\n                        Kraft Heinz Company\n                    \n                \n                Contact\n                Investor Login\n            \n        \n        \n        \n            \n                \n                    \n                        PARTNERS\n                    \n                    \n                        \n                            Bernardo Hees\n                        \n                            Partner of 3G Capital since July 2010\n                            CEO of The Kraft Heinz Company since June 2013\n                            CEO and Board Member of Burger King Corporation from 2010 to June 2013\n                            CEO of America Latina Logistica (ALL) from 2005 to September 2010 (previously worked\n                                as COO, OPM, CFO, Commercial Officer and Analyst)\n                            MBA from University of Warwick in England\n                        \n                    \n                    \n                        \n                            Bernardo Piquet\n                        \n                            Joined 3G Capital in July 2005, becoming a Partner in January 2008\n                            Senior Vice President at Safra National Bank of New York\n                            NYSE (New York Stock Exchange) Senior Consultant\n                            MS from State University of New York at Stony Brook, NY\n                            BS in Computer Engineering from PUC, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil\n                        \n                    \n                    \n                        \n                            Claudio Bahbout\n                        \n                            Joined 3G Capital in April 2004, becoming a Partner in January 2010\n                            Previously worked for JGP, a hedge fund based in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil from 2002\n                                to 2004\n                            MS in Finance from Funda\u00e7\u00e3o Get\u00falio Vargas\n                            BS in Economics from Instituto Brasileiro de Mercados e Capitais\n                        \n                    \n                    \n                        \n                            Daniel Dreyfus\n                        \n                            Partner at 3G Capital since February 2013\n                            Portfolio Manager Goldman Sachs Investment Partners and Goldman Sachs Principal\n                                Strategies from 2000 - 2012. Managed the fund's natural resources investments.\n                            DLJ Investment Banking analyst from 1998 - 2000 in the natural resources group.\n                            BCom McGill University, 1998\n                        \n                    \n                    \n                        \n                            Daniel Schwartz\n                        \n                            Joined 3G Capital in February 2005, becoming a Partner in January 2008\n                            CEO of Restaurant Brands International since December 2014; previously CEO of Burger King from June 2013 to December 2014; CFO of Burger King from January 2011 to June 2013\n                            Previously worked for Altair Capital Management, a Stamford, CT based hedge fund,\n                                from 2003 to 2004\n                            Analyst in the Mergers & Acquisitions group at Credit Suisse First\n                                Boston from 2001 to 2003\n                            BS in Applied Economics and Management from Cornell University\n                        \n                    \n                    \n                        \n                            Josh Klivan\n                        \n                            Joined 3G Capital in June 2008, becoming a Partner in January 2011\n                            BS in Economics from the Wharton School at the University of Pennsylvania\n                        \n                    \n                    \n                        \n                            Munir Javeri\n                        \n                            Partner at 3G Capital since June 2011\n                            Global Head of Trading at MF Global from January - June 2011\n                            Partner and Portfolio Manager at Gandhara Advisors, London/Hong Kong from 2006 to\n                                2009\n                            Principal at J. Goldfield & Co from 2004 - 2006\n                            Vice-President Soros Fund Management from 2003 - 2004\n                            Associate at Oak Investment Partners from 2000 - 2003\n                            BS in Electrical Engineering from Massachusetts Institute of Technology 2000\n                        \n                    \n                    \n                        \n                            Paulo Basilio\n                        \n                            Partner at 3G Capital since July 2012\n                            CFO of The Kraft Heinz Company since June 2013\n                            CEO of America Latina Logistica (ALL) from 2010 to September 2012 (previously worked\n                                as COO, CFO, Commercial Officer and Analyst)\n                            M.Sc. in Economics at Fundacao Getulio Vargas\n                        \n                    \n                    \n                        \n                            Pedro Drevon\n                        \n                            Joined 3G Capital in April 2008, becoming a Partner in January 2011\n                            Previously worked as an equity analyst for BBM Bank, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil from\n                                2007 to 2008\n                            BS in Industrial Engineering from Ecole Centrale, France\n                            BS in Electric Engineering from PUC, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil\n                        \n                    \n                    \n                        \n                            Anuroop Duggal\n                        \n                            Joined 3G Capital in February 2013, becoming a Partner in January 2015\n                            Previously worked for Goldman Sachs Investment Partners from 2007 to 2012 \n                            BS in Electrical Engineering and BA in Business Administration from Western Ontario, 2007\n                        \n                    \n                    \n                        \n                            Marcos Romaneiro\n                        \n                            Joined 3G Capital in January 2012, becoming a Partner in January 2015 \n                            Asia Pacific Zone President of The Kraft Heinz Company since June 2014; previously SVP Finance from June 2013 to June 2014\n                            Prior to 3G Capital, worked for Vestar Capital Partners and Cerberus Capital Management\n                            Bachelor's Degree in Business Economics from Brown University\n                        \n                    \n                    \n                        \n                            David Knopf\n                        \n                            Joined 3G Capital in October 2013, becoming a Partner in July 2015\n                            Prior to 3G Capital, worked for Goldman Sachs and Onex Partners\n                            Bachelor's degree in Economics from Princeton University\n                        \n                    \n                    \n                \n                \n            \n            \n            \n                \n                    \n                    Anuroop Duggal\n                    Bernardo Hees\n                    Bernardo Piquet\n                    Claudio Bahbout\n                    Daniel Dreyfus\n                    David Knopf\n                    Daniel Schwartz\n                    Joshua Klivan\n                    Marcos Romaneiro\n                    Munir Javeri\n                    Paulo Basilio\n                    Pedro Drevon\n                \n            \n            \n        \n        \n        \n        \n    \n    \n    \n        \n            Copyright \u00a9 2010-                                            var theDate = new Date();\n                                            document.write(theDate.getFullYear()); \n                3G Capital. All Rights Reserved. | Legal Notices and Terms of Use.", "page": ["3G Capital - Partners"]}
{"text": "About\n                Approach\n                Partners\n                    \n                        Founding Partners\n                        Partners\n                    \n                \n                Acquisitions\n                    \n                        Burger King\n                        H.J. Heinz Company\n                        Restaurant Brands International\n                        Kraft Heinz Company\n                    \n                \n                Contact\n                Investor Login\n            \n        \n        \n        \n            \n                \n                    \n                        H.J. Heinz Company\n                    \n                    \n                        PITTSBURGH, OMAHA and NEW YORK \u2013 June 7, 2013 \u2013 H.J. Heinz Company (NYSE: HNZ)\n                        (\u201cHeinz\u201d) today announced the completion of its previously announced acquisition by an investment consortium comprised of Berkshire Hathaway and an investment fund affiliated with 3G Capital. The acquisition agreement was first announced on February 14 and the transaction closed and became effective today. \n                    \n                        Under the terms of the agreement, which has been unanimously approved by Heinz\u2019s\n                        Board of Directors, Heinz shareholders will receive $72.50 in cash for each share\n                        of common stock they own, in a transaction valued at $28 billion, including the\n                        assumption of Heinz\u2019s outstanding debt. The per share price represents a 20% premium\n                        to Heinz\u2019s closing share price of $60.48 on February 13, 2013, a 19% premium to\n                        Heinz\u2019s all-time high share price, a 23% premium to the 90-day average Heinz share\n                        price and a 30% premium to the one-year average share price.\n                    \n                    \n                    \n                    \n                        Visit the Heinz web site: www.heinz.com\n                    \n                    \n                    \n                    \n                        View the press release\n                    \n                \n                \n            \n            \n        \n        \n        \n        \n    \n    \n    \n        \n            Copyright \u00a9 2010-                                            var theDate = new Date();\n                                            document.write(theDate.getFullYear()); \n                3G Capital. All Rights Reserved. | Legal Notices and Terms of Use.", "page": ["3G Capital - H.J. Heinz Company"]}
{"text": "About\n                Approach\n                Partners\n                    \n                        Founding Partners\n                        Partners\n                    \n                \n                Acquisitions\n                    \n                        Burger King\n                        H.J. Heinz Company\n                        Restaurant Brands International\n                        Kraft Heinz Company\n                    \n                \n                Contact\n                Investor Login\n            \n        \n        \n        \n            \n                \n                    \n                        APPROACH\n                    \n                        3G Capital's strategy is to identify and invest in opportunities that are well-positioned\n                            for profitable, long-term growth and success across a variety of different sectors\n                            and regions. The firm's management team leverages prior investment experience, industry\n                            expertise and an extensive global network to successfully implement this strategy.\n                        3G Capital's core management philosophy focuses on developing and retaining top\n                            tier talent.\n                        3G Capital and its affiliates have particular expertise in the retail and consumer\n                            sector and consistently evaluate new opportunities for successful investments in\n                            this industry.\n                        In order to preserve capital and maximize value, 3G Capital believes that factoring\n                            in the downside of an investment is equally as important as the upside potential.\n                            This philosophy has helped the firm weather various global economic cycles.\n                        3G Capital operates as a true partnership with strong meritocracy, and therefore\n                            there is significant alignment of interests among 3G Capital's Principals & Partners\n                            and relevant management teams.\n                    \n                \n                \n            \n            \n        \n        \n        \n        \n    \n    \n    \n        \n            Copyright \u00a9 2010-                                            var theDate = new Date();\n                                            document.write(theDate.getFullYear()); \n                3G Capital. All Rights Reserved. | Legal Notices and Terms of Use.", "page": ["3G Capital - Approach"]}
{"text": "About\n                Approach\n                Partners\n                    \n                        Founding Partners\n                        Partners\n                    \n                \n                Acquisitions\n                    \n                        Burger King\n                        H.J. Heinz Company\n                        Restaurant Brands International\n                        Kraft Heinz Company\n                    \n                \n                Contact\n                Investor Login\n            \n        \n        \n        \n            \n                \n                    ABOUT\n                    \n                        3G Capital is a global investment firm focused on long-term value, with a particular\n                        emphasis on maximizing the potential of brands and businesses. The firm and its\n                        partners have a strong history of operational excellence, board involvement, deep\n                        sector expertise, and an extensive global network. 3G Capital works in close partnership\n                        with management teams at its portfolio companies and places a strong emphasis on\n                        recruiting, developing and retaining top-tier talent.\n                    \n                    \n                        The Founding Partners of 3G Capital are Jorge Paulo Lemann, Marcel Telles, Carlos Alberto Sicupira, Roberto Thompson, and Alex Behring, our Managing Partner, all of whom have together been investing in and operating businesses for several decades. The firm has offices in New York City and Rio de Janeiro.\n                    \n                    \n                        Most recently, in July 2015, 3G Capital partnered with Berkshire Hathaway to complete the combination of H.J. Heinz Company and Kraft Foods Group, forming the Kraft Heinz Company, following 3G and Berkshire\u2019s acquisition of Heinz in June 2013.  Previously, in December 2014, 3G Capital completed the combination of Burger King and Tim Hortons, forming Restaurant Brands International, following 3G\u2019s acquisition of Burger King in October 2010.  Affiliates of 3G\u2019s Partners are meaningful shareholders of AB Inbev since 1989 and Lojas Americanas since 1983.\n                    \n\n                \n                \n            \n            \n        \n        \n        \n        \n    \n    \n    \n        \n            Copyright \u00a9 2010-                                            var theDate = new Date();\n                                            document.write(theDate.getFullYear()); \n                3G Capital. All Rights Reserved. | Legal Notices and Terms of Use.", "page": ["3G Capital - About"]}
